import React from 'react'
  import { MDXTag } from '@mdx-js/tag'
  import { Playground, PropsTable } from 'docz'
import Mono from './index';

export default class MDXContent extends React.Component {
  constructor(props) {
    super(props)
    this.layout = null
  }
  render() {
    const { components, ...props } = this.props

    return <MDXTag
             name="wrapper"
             
             components={components}>
<MDXTag name="h1" components={components} props={{"id":"mono"}}>{`Mono`}</MDXTag>
<MDXTag name="p" components={components}>{`This styles text as monospaced. It can be used inline (ie it's not a block level element).`}</MDXTag>
<MDXTag name="h2" components={components} props={{"id":"basic-usage"}}>{`Basic usage`}</MDXTag>
<Playground __codesandbox={`undefined`} __position={0} __code={'<Mono>This class uses our mono font-family.</Mono>'} __scope={{props: this ? this.props : props,Mono}}>
    <Mono>
        This class uses our mono font-family.
    </Mono>
</Playground>
<MDXTag name="h2" components={components} props={{"id":"properties"}}>{`Properties`}</MDXTag>
<PropsTable of={Mono} />
           </MDXTag>
  }
}
